# Pretty per-user URLs -> serve the page (JS reads the name from the path).
# 200 = rewrite (browser keeps the pretty URL). Destinations use the CLEAN paths
# (/stats not /stats.html) because Cloudflare Pages 301-redirects *.html to the
# extensionless URL, which would bounce /user/<name>/stats to /stats.
/user/:name/stats     /stats      200
/user/:name/coasters  /coasters   200
/user/:name           /stats      200
